## Presenting My Research at the UGA REU Symposium

This summer I had the opportunity to participate in the University of Georgia Research Experience for Undergraduates (REU) in Crop Genetics and Genomics.

During the symposium I presented my research poster summarizing the project and the methods I used throughout the summer. I am beyond grateful for the opportunity 
to learn from such awesome mentors in the Jim Leebens Mack lab. I had so much fun expanding on my skill sets in computational biology and learning how to use those
skill sets to analyze plant genomics. Alongside my computational project I also had a greenhouse experiment that I really enjoyed. 
